issue_body:
We have a model with range having min/max values being the same. (An initial setting for future growth of range without using different types.)  This is rejected by pyang.  Trying other validator like yanger, that's not rejected.   It may be caused by a minor comparison setting in types.py:is_smaller? For example,

leaf name-index {
  type uint32 {
    range "1..1";
  }
  description "Group name index";
}

Archive: agi.py
Bug Python 3 at Line: 128
        return ''.join(['"', string.encode('utf8', 'ignore'), '"'])

Correction:
return ''.join(['"', string.encode('ascii', 'ignore').decode('ascii'), '"'])

