Hey, I've stumbled upon an unexpected behaviour when using `x-nullable` 

My swagger definition:
```
...
        "SomeObject": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
                "data": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "required": [
                        "type"
                    ],
                    "properties": {
                        "type": {
                            "type": "string"
                        },
                        "attributes": {
                            "type": "object",
                            "properties": {
                                "name": {
                                    "type": "string"
                                },
                                "value": {
                                    "type": "string"
                                },
                                "nullable_field": {
                                    "type": "string",
                                    "x-nullable": true
                                }
                            }
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
        }
...
```
From what is stated in [bravado-core documentation](http://bravado-core.readthedocs.io/en/latest/models.html#allowing-null-values-for-properties) I should be able to send in my request `None` as a value of `nullable_field` but sadly that's not the case, `nullable_field` simply doesn't exist in the generated payload. 

I've traced the issue to `marshal_object` method, where if the value of the field is `None` and this field is not required, then the field is simply omitted. This is inconsistent with documentation, where there is no mention that field has to be a required field in order for this to work - even more, in example in documentation field that is being set to null is also not required.

If I'm right and this is a bug I'll be happy to submit PR with a fix, and if not could you explain why it is implemented in this way?

